<package >
  <metadata>
    <id>Log4net.Appender.Watchr</id>
    <version>2014.03.23</version>
    <title>WatchR Appender For Log4Net</title>
    <authors>mxrss</authors>
    <owners>LogicStructure</owners>
    <projectUrl>http://michaeltroth.com/watchr</projectUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <summary>Get instant insight into what your console app is doing on remote servers.</summary>
    <description>Want to see what your console app is doing or your website without having to 
    RDP into the server. Or have a constant connection to PowershellRemoting? Now, you can
  View what is going real time. Distribute your link to your team mates and start seeing problems
  before operations gives you the go ahead to look at logs. Checkout the project site if you want to contribute
  or host your own version of the software.</description>
    <releaseNotes>
      Initial commit, contains ability to add create a new watchr endpoint and set it up in your log4net appender to view.
    </releaseNotes>
